    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.8.0-dev+96-gd9dcfd021\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 12.2\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.25.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nfunction Print_range()\r\n    local pos = {\r\n        start = vim.fn.getpos(\"'<\"),\r\n        [\"end\"] = vim.fn.getpos(\"'>\"),\r\n    }\r\n    vim.pretty_print(pos)\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set({ \"n\", \"x\" }, \"<leader>v\", Print_range)\r\nvim.keymap.set({ \"n\", \"x\" }, \"<leader>V\", \":lua Print_range()<cr>\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nenter visual mode on line 1 and use `<leader>v`\r\nenter visual mode on line 2 and use `<leader>V`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nthe two mappings behave identically in visual mode.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nwhen using the callback mapping during visual mode, visual range position is not updated.\r\n\r\nit would be nice to control the execution of the callback as if it was executed using `\":<C-u>call luaref()<cr>\"` versus `\"<cmd>call luaref()<cr>\"`",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
