            "body": "@clason \r\n>Yes, because : enters command mode (as opposed to <cmd>, see :h <Cmd>), so these two mappings are in fact not equivalent.\r\n\r\nI know, but you can in fact control the behavior when using \"old-style\" mappings. This is not controllable when using callbacks.\r\n\r\nThis invalidates visual-mode mappings that leverage callbacks and closures. The point of visual-mode mappings is indeed to _know_ where visual selection starts/ends",
